message: Made PneumaticCraft open source!:D Have fun!
Added dev instructions, and added API package to be generated.
Hidden the fact that I copied BluePower's API gradle task :P
Refactored Omnidirectional Hopper, fixes #178 , Omnidirectional Hopper eating items from JABBA barrels
Added some info on how to get forge running
Different link formatting - is this better?
small change to the links, again
big changeover for MC1.12 - now maintained by desht

Big tube module commit!
- Tube modules now rendering properly.  Went back to simple models in
  code with TESR instead of trying to render .obj models
- To fix:  little glitchiness remains with hitbox detection in some
  cases - ray tracing is off somewhere.

Semiblock placement now works.  Heat frame tested & working well.
- can now also use pneumatic wrench to remove semiblock frames

Assembly controller now renders
- using JSON model for base & connectors, TESR for rotating screen

Fixed logistics drone crash
- logistics drone are basically working now, but not well tested

Flux compressor is a thing again
Just a simple textured cube for now, I lack the modelling skillz sadly
Universal sensor now works (both rendering and functionality)

Heat sinks now tint properly according to temperature
Redid the heat sink model with JSON so tintindex works

CoFH integration
- PneumaticCraft fuels now work in the Compression Dynamo
- Gasoline is equivalent to CoFH Refined Fuel
- CoFH crude oil now works in the Refinery

Fix a small typo in README.md.

Also rearrange the dep section in the Gradle build file.

Signed-off-by: Kamran Mackey <kamranm1200@gmail.com>
Added a little licensing info to README

Build changes:
- Build number is now included in artifacts JAR names
  (build number is 'CUSTOM' if built by hand)
- Fix API class files not being included in main JAR
README update including API relicense under LGPLv3
